2:["$","h4",null,{"id":"third-party","className":"mb-3","children":"Third-Party Products and Services"}]
3:["$","p",null,{"className":"mb-4","children":"This website may contain information about, or links to, third-party products, services, and technologies including but not limited to Cisco, HP, Aruba, Hikvision, D-Link, TP-Link, Milestone Systems, and other manufacturers and software vendors. KFLR is an authorized reseller and integrator for many of these brands, but we are not the manufacturer or developer of these products."}]
4:["$","p",null,{"className":"mb-4","children":"All product names, logos, brands, trademarks, and registered trademarks are property of their respective owners. All company, product and service names used in this website are for identification purposes only. Use of these names, logos, and brands does not imply endorsement by the respective trademark holders."}]
5:["$","p",null,{"className":"mb-5","children":"While we strive to provide accurate information about third-party products, specifications, features, and compatibility may change without notice. We recommend verifying all technical specifications directly with the manufacturer before making purchase decisions. KFLR is not responsible for changes to third-party products, discontinuation of products, or manufacturer warranty policies."}]
6:["$","h4",null,{"id":"technical-accuracy","className":"mb-3","children":"Technical Accuracy and Changes"}]
7:["$","p",null,{"className":"mb-4","children":"The information technology industry evolves rapidly. Product specifications, software versions, compatibility requirements, security vulnerabilities, and best practices change frequently. While we make every effort to keep our website content current and accurate, there may be delays in updating information to reflect the latest changes."}]
8:["$","p",null,{"className":"mb-5","children":"Technical information, configuration examples, command-line syntax, and troubleshooting guides provided on this website are based on our experience and testing at the time of publication. However, different hardware revisions, firmware versions, operating system updates, and network environments may produce different results. We strongly recommend testing all configurations in a non-production environment before deployment and maintaining proper backups before making any system changes."}]
9:["$","h4",null,{"id":"service-availability","className":"mb-3","children":"Service Availability and Performance"}]
a:["$","p",null,{"className":"mb-4","children":"While we strive for 99.9% uptime for our managed services and support contracts, we do not guarantee uninterrupted or error-free service availability. Factors beyond our control, including but not limited to natural disasters, power outages, internet service provider issues, cyber attacks, hardware failures, and force majeure events may cause service interruptions."}]
b:["$","p",null,{"className":"mb-5","children":"Performance metrics, speed improvements, cost savings, and efficiency gains mentioned on this website are based on typical scenarios and historical data from our client engagements. Actual results will vary depending on your specific environment, existing infrastructure, usage patterns, and numerous other factors. Past performance and results achieved for other clients do not guarantee similar outcomes for your organization."}]
c:["$","h4",null,{"id":"security","className":"mb-3","children":"Security and Data Protection"}]
d:["$","p",null,{"className":"mb-4","children":"While we implement industry-standard security measures to protect your data and our systems, no method of transmission over the Internet or method of electronic storage is 100% secure. We cannot guarantee absolute security of data transmitted to or stored on our systems or through our services."}]
e:["$","p",null,{"className":"mb-4","children":"Cybersecurity threats evolve constantly, and new vulnerabilities are discovered regularly. Even with firewalls, intrusion prevention systems, antivirus software, and other security controls in place, there is no such thing as perfect security. Organizations must maintain a layered defense-in-depth approach, regular security assessments, employee training, and incident response capabilities."}]
f:["$","p",null,{"className":"mb-5","children":"KFLR provides security solutions and recommendations based on industry best practices and our professional experience. However, the ultimate responsibility for your organization's security posture, compliance with regulations, and protection of sensitive data rests with your organization and designated personnel."}]
10:["$","h4",null,{"id":"warranties","className":"mb-3","children":"Limitation of Warranties"}]
11:["$","p",null,{"className":"mb-3","children":"KFLR makes no warranties or representations about the accuracy or completeness of this website's content or the content of any websites linked to this website. We assume no liability or responsibility for any:"}]
